{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a3f7c2e1-4b8d-4e9a-b1d6-7f3c2e8a5b04",
    "name": "Weather Middleware Platform — Demo (Medellín)",
    "description": "Colección de demo para el Weather Middleware Platform.\n\n**Flujo recomendado para la demo:**\n1. Health checks en ambos servicios\n2. Crear ubicación (Medellín)\n3. Disparar ingesta manual\n4. Listar observaciones crudas\n5. Crear reglas de alerta\n6. Disparar procesamiento\n7. Ver observaciones procesadas\n8. Ver alertas generadas\n9. Acknowledge de una alerta\n\n**Variables de entorno:**\n- `ingestion_url` → http://localhost:8000\n- `processing_url` → http://localhost:8001\n- `api_key` → local-dev-key",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "ingestion_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "processing_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8001",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "api_key",
      "value": "local-dev-key",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "location_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Se autocompleta al crear la ubicación de Medellín"
    },
    {
      "key": "observation_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Se autocompleta al listar observaciones"
    },
    {
      "key": "rule_id_temp",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Se autocompleta al crear la regla de temperatura"
    },
    {
      "key": "rule_id_humidity",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Se autocompleta al crear la regla de humedad"
    },
    {
      "key": "processed_obs_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Se autocompleta al listar observaciones procesadas"
    },
    {
      "key": "alert_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Se autocompleta al listar alertas"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 · Health Checks",
      "description": "Verifica que ambos servicios están activos. Siempre empezar aquí.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Ingestion Service — Health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Verifica que el ingestion-service y su conexión a Postgres están OK."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Ingestion service is healthy', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Processing Service — Health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{processing_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{processing_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Verifica que el processing-service y su conexión a Postgres están OK."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Processing service is healthy', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02 · Locations (Ingestion Service)",
      "description": "CRUD completo de ubicaciones. Creamos Medellín como ubicación principal y otras ciudades colombianas para enriquecer la demo.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Listar ubicaciones",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/locations?active_only=false",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "locations"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "active_only",
                  "value": "false",
                  "description": "true para ver solo ubicaciones activas"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Lista todas las ubicaciones registradas. No requiere API key."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Crear ubicación — Medellín ⭐",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Medellín, Colombia\",\n  \"latitude\": 6.2442,\n  \"longitude\": -75.5812,\n  \"timezone\": \"America/Bogota\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/locations",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "locations"]
            },
            "description": "Registra Medellín como ubicación de monitoreo.\n\nCoordinadas reales: 6.2442° N, 75.5812° W\nZona horaria: America/Bogota (UTC-5)\n\n**Requiere X-API-Key.** El ID se guarda automáticamente en la variable `location_id`."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Location created with 201', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json && json.id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('location_id', json.id);",
                  "    console.log('✅ location_id guardado:', json.id);",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has required fields', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('id');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('name');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.latitude).to.eql(6.2442);",
                  "    pm.expect(json.longitude).to.eql(-75.5812);",
                  "    pm.expect(json.is_active).to.be.true;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Crear ubicación — Bogotá",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Bogotá, Colombia\",\n  \"latitude\": 4.7110,\n  \"longitude\": -74.0721,\n  \"timezone\": \"America/Bogota\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/locations",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "locations"]
            },
            "description": "Registra Bogotá como segunda ubicación de monitoreo. Útil para demostrar que el scheduler ingesta múltiples ciudades en paralelo."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Crear ubicación — Cartagena",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Cartagena, Colombia\",\n  \"latitude\": 10.3910,\n  \"longitude\": -75.4794,\n  \"timezone\": \"America/Bogota\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/locations",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "locations"]
            },
            "description": "Registra Cartagena — ciudad costera con temperaturas más altas, útil para disparar alertas de temperatura."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Obtener ubicación por ID",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/locations/{{location_id}}",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "locations", "{{location_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Obtiene el detalle de la ubicación de Medellín. Usa la variable `location_id` capturada en el POST."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Actualizar ubicación — cambiar nombre",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Medellín (Ciudad de la Eterna Primavera)\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/locations/{{location_id}}",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "locations", "{{location_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Actualización parcial (PATCH semántico via PUT). Solo se envían los campos que cambian — los demás se mantienen. Útil para demostrar el `LocationUpdateDTO` con campos opcionales."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Desactivar ubicación (soft delete)",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/locations/{{location_id}}",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "locations", "{{location_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "⚠️ Soft delete — no elimina el registro, solo pone `is_active = false`. Las observaciones históricas permanecen intactas y la FK de `raw_observations` no se rompe (ondelete=RESTRICT). Retorna 204 No Content.\n\n**Nota para la demo:** ejecutar solo al final para no perder los datos de Medellín."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Listar ubicaciones activas solamente",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/locations?active_only=true",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "locations"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "active_only",
                  "value": "true"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Útil después del soft delete para demostrar que Medellín ya no aparece en la lista de activas."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "[Error] Crear ubicación sin API key → 401",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Cali, Colombia\",\n  \"latitude\": 3.4516,\n  \"longitude\": -76.5320,\n  \"timezone\": \"America/Bogota\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/locations",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "locations"]
            },
            "description": "Demuestra que los endpoints de escritura están protegidos. Sin el header `X-API-Key` debe retornar **401 Unauthorized**."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Rejects request without API key (401)', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(401);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Error] Crear ubicación con coordenadas inválidas → 422",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Ubicación inválida\",\n  \"latitude\": 999.0,\n  \"longitude\": -75.5812,\n  \"timezone\": \"America/Bogota\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/locations",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "locations"]
            },
            "description": "Demuestra la validación de Pydantic. La latitud debe estar en [-90, 90]. FastAPI retorna automáticamente **422 Unprocessable Entity** con el detalle del campo que falló."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Validates latitude range (422)', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(422);",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.detail[0].loc).to.include('latitude');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "03 · Observations — Ingesta (Ingestion Service)",
      "description": "Ingesta manual y consulta de observaciones crudas desde Open-Meteo.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Disparar ingesta manual ⭐",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/observations/ingest",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "observations", "ingest"]
            },
            "description": "Dispara el use case de ingesta inmediatamente, sin esperar el scheduler (que corre cada 900s por defecto).\n\nHace un fetch real a la API de Open-Meteo para todas las ubicaciones activas y persiste las observaciones. El upsert con `on_conflict_do_nothing` garantiza idempotencia — si ya existe una observación para ese `(location_id, observed_at)` no se duplica.\n\nRetorna: `{ locations_processed, observations_stored, errors }`"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Ingestion returns 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "console.log('📥 Ingesta:', json.observations_stored, 'observaciones en', json.locations_processed, 'ubicaciones');",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('No errors during ingestion', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.errors).to.have.lengthOf(0);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Listar observaciones de Medellín",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/observations?location_id={{location_id}}&limit=20&offset=0",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "observations"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "location_id",
                  "value": "{{location_id}}",
                  "description": "Filtra por Medellín"
                },
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "20"
                },
                {
                  "key": "offset",
                  "value": "0"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Lista las observaciones crudas de Medellín con paginación.\n\nResponde con `{ items, total, limit, offset }`. Cada item contiene temperatura, humedad, viento, precipitación y código de tiempo de Open-Meteo."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Returns paginated observations', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('items');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('total');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.items && json.items.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('observation_id', json.items[0].id);",
                  "    console.log('✅ observation_id guardado:', json.items[0].id);",
                  "    console.log('🌡️  Temperatura Medellín:', json.items[0].temperature_c, '°C');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Listar todas las observaciones (sin filtro)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/observations?limit=50&offset=0",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "observations"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "50"
                },
                {
                  "key": "offset",
                  "value": "0"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Ve todas las observaciones de todas las ciudades. Útil para mostrar que el scheduler procesa múltiples ubicaciones."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Obtener observación por ID",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/observations/{{observation_id}}",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "observations", "{{observation_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Obtiene el detalle de una observación específica. La variable `observation_id` se capturó automáticamente en el request anterior."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Disparar ingesta 2 veces — idempotencia",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{ingestion_url}}/api/v1/observations/ingest",
              "host": ["{{ingestion_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "observations", "ingest"]
            },
            "description": "Ejecutar este request inmediatamente después del anterior.\n\n**Punto clave para la demo:** `observations_stored` debe ser **0** porque todas las observaciones ya existen. El `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` de PostgreSQL garantiza idempotencia sin race conditions."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Idempotent: 0 observations stored on second call', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.observations_stored).to.eql(0);",
                  "    console.log('✅ Idempotencia confirmada: observations_stored =', json.observations_stored);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "04 · Rules — Reglas de Alerta (Processing Service)",
      "description": "CRUD de reglas de procesamiento. Las reglas definen qué métricas monitorear y qué severidad asignar cuando se supera un umbral.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Listar reglas",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{processing_url}}/api/v1/rules",
              "host": ["{{processing_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "rules"]
            },
            "description": "Lista todas las reglas de procesamiento (activas e inactivas)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Crear regla — Temperatura alta ⭐",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"metric\": \"temperature_c\",\n  \"operator\": \">\",\n  \"threshold\": 28.0,\n  \"severity\": \"MEDIUM\",\n  \"alert_type\": \"HIGH_TEMPERATURE\",\n  \"message_template\": \"Temperatura en Medellín: {value}°C supera el umbral de {threshold}°C\",\n  \"is_active\": true\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{processing_url}}/api/v1/rules",
              "host": ["{{processing_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "rules"]
            },
            "description": "Crea una regla que genera alerta MEDIUM cuando la temperatura supera los 28°C.\n\nMedellín tiene temperatura promedio de 22-27°C, pero días cálidos pueden superar 28°C, lo que hace esta regla realista para disparar alertas en la demo.\n\n`metric` puede ser: `temperature_c`, `humidity_pct`, `wind_speed_kmh`, `precipitation_mm`, `heat_index_c`, `wind_chill_c`, `feels_like_c`\n\n`operator` válidos: `>`, `>=`, `<`, `<=`, `==`\n\n`severity` válidos: `LOW`, `MEDIUM`, `HIGH`, `CRITICAL`"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Rule created with 201', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json && json.id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('rule_id_temp', json.id);",
                  "    console.log('✅ rule_id_temp guardado:', json.id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Crear regla — Temperatura crítica",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
